  "system": {
    "biography": {
      "value": "<p>Cyclones control space by making it uncomfortable to occupy. Buffeting Winds keeps melee fighters pushed back while Wind Strike punishes anyone who closes. Against spellcasters and archers they use their speed to negate distance. The Momentum Defense makes them genuinely difficult to hit while moving, so they rarely stop moving. A summoner who needs a chokepoint held by something that cannot itself be easily held will find them useful.</p>"
    },
